content.description: Start on the rail in the pit, move up crimps to get to a bomber incut crimp (avoid the broken flake). Finish up towards the right. Height will certainly be an advantage.
content.protection: The landing is very sketchy since the problem starts in the pit. Lots of pads and spotters needed.
content.location: This boulder is located just left of Group Leader.

content.description: From a sit work up fun seams and balance your way to the top.  A fun line.  The stands a little easier and fun too.
content.protection: a few pads.  It's a little rocky.
content.location: On the Nature Walk face.  From the North shore this Face is the biggest boulder facing you in the first open talus field you reach.

content.description: From a sit start on low good holds do a few fun moves and topout.
content.location: If walking from the north shore this boulder is the biggest one facing you in the first open talus field you reach.  The arete is the farthest to the right.

content.description: Start on a good slopey right hand sidepull and left hand on downpulling sloper.  Go directly up the right arete of Group Leader using a series of bump moves possibly and punch to the jug.  Fun.  Essentially the same start as group leader.
content.protection: A few pads and a spotter.  There is a ledge drop off that could be dangerous.

content.description: Fun jugs on the right side of the Nature Walk face.
Awesome tall line up the tallest part of the face with the crux about 2/3 the way up, squeezing up a mini bulge. There is a committing throw to the lip. Really fun climbing.
content.location: On the Group Leader Boulder. Around to the right of Group Leader and Like a Boss. This line goes straight up the tallest part of the face.

content.description: Starts on the good rail for your right hand and a crimp for your left.  Slap your way up each side and end it with a nice heel hook to the finishing jug.
content.location: Walking from the North Shore this is in the first big talus field that opens up.  It's on the left side in amongst some big rocks.  More potential surrounding the area.

content.description: On the Left side of the Nature Walk Face.  From a stand start at the bottom of the slab ramp follow the Left trending seam around the corner above the drop off and top out as for Like a Boss and Group Leader.
content.protection: A few pads and someone to throw pads around the corner for the topout

content.description: Stand start matched on the left arete. A handful of interesting and powerful moves lead out of the overhang.
content.location: Hidden just behind the topout of "Six Feet Under"

content.description: Go up creaky holds in the center of the Nature Walk face.  Good movement on kinda sketchy holds.  Be careful, the landing is weird.
content.location: Center of the Nature Walk Face.

content.description:
SDS under the overhang. Right hand on the lip and left hand on a perfect crimp in the crack. Get a high right heel hook (you've been going to yoga, right?) and you're off. Fun moves through a bulge over the lip and an unusually grippy top-out. 

  The crux is probably finding a spot for your tush, followed by the heel hook. After that, it's party time.
content.location: ~20 yards north of the Group Leader boulder, and up the talus field a bit. See photos

content.description: Bouldering above the Tumbled Rocks near the “Baraboo Quartzite” sign, which is about a hundred yards south of the North Shore Beach along the Tumbled Rocks Trail.
